4,/Hotel_Review-g186338-d1097114-Reviews-or0-CityStay_Hotel-London_England.html#REVIEWS,"CityStay Hotel Reviews, London",loved the sheets,"Stayed here at short notice after unexpectedly taken ill and being unable to get to our original destination. The hotel may not be in the most salubrious of places but let's not forget it is in Bow and for me it was perfect. The young man on the desk was helpful and we were given an en-suite room to the rear. It was neat and clean and those bed sheets felt like silk. The shower room was narrow but functional and clean. Breakfast was included in the price which made this a very cheap deal. The breakfast room is down a narrow set of stairs and you just help yourself. I would suggest that this is not the ideal place to stay if you are physically disabled. I read on some of the reviews about a police station being opposite the hotel and hence being noisy. The police station is actually some way along the road and in our experience the siren noises were more to do with ambulances. I think it needs to be remembered, this is an inner city location and it is cheap. Close proximity to tube station means it could be used as a cheap option to explore London. Overall we were happy and would stay here again.…",Date of stay: November 2018,4.0
